BOREO.HE.summary: Boreo Oyj imports and sells electronic components and tools to Finland, Russia, and the Baltics. The company offers 3D printing products, antennas and accessories, audio/video products, cables and accessories, converters, KVMs, networking products, PC and car accessories, telecommunication and power products, wall outlets, and AVs. It also provides batteries, chemicals, connectors, cooling products and fans, development kits, electric accessories, LED components, lighting and RF products, mechanical components, passives, relays, semiconductors, sounders, switches, tapes, and literature products. In addition, the company offers baking ovens, cable cutting and strip tools, cleaning and dry storage products, clothing and personal protection products, component counter and lead handling products, crimping dies and machines, dispensers, fume extractors, labels, lamps, microscopes, mounting accessories, PCBs and accessories, packing products, safety and soldering products, ultrasonic cleaners, and weighting products, as well as ESD and protection products. Further, it provides air quality/flow meters, bags and carrying cases, battery testers, cable locators and testers, calipers, clamp and distance meters, component and earth ground testers, electrical and FO testers, endoscopes, frequency counters, function generators, installation and insulation testers, IR windows, lasers, LAN and machine testers, light intensity meters, loggers, multimeters and its related software, oscilloscopes, phase rotation indicators, power quality meters, process calibrators and precision pressure gauges, radiation meters, solar power and sound level meters, power analyzers, surface testers, tachometers, temperature/humidity meters, test leads and probes, thermal cameras and accessories, vibration testers, and visual inspection and other tools. It sells products through stores and catalogues. The company was formerly known as Yleiselektroniikka Oyj. Boreo Oyj was founded in 1969 and is based in Espoo, Finland.

ENEDO.HE.summary: Enedo Oyj engages in the design and manufacture of DC power systems, AC/DC power supplies, and LED drivers for telecom, industrial, medical, lighting, utility, and military industries. It offers power system products, such as AC and rail power systems, power system components, and legacy products; power supply products, including, configurable multi-output, high power LED, and medical grade power supplies, as well as battery chargers, DC UPS back-up power products, DC/DC converters, DC/AC inverters, and custom solutions. The company also provides constant current, constant voltage, and programmable LED drivers. It serves in North, Central, and South America, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, Asia, and the Pacific. The company was formerly known as Efore Oyj and changed its name to Enedo Oyj in February 2020. Enedo Oyj was founded in 1975 and is headquartered in Vantaa, Finland.

REKA.HE.summary: Reka Industrial Oyj manufactures and sells cables in Finland, Sweden, Denmark, Norway, the Baltic countries, and Russia. It offers instrumentation cables, fire-resistant cables, medium and high voltage cables, halogen-free cables, network power cables, and standard cables under the FlameRex, DryRex, LiteRex, PoweRex, and Reka brands. The company serves construction, power distribution, and equipment manufacturers. The company was formerly known as Neo Industrial Plc and changed its name to Reka Industrial Oyj in December 2020.
